Package com.dukes.lang.parser.node Description

Stores all the necessary classes to implement an abstract syntax tree. This is shown in the AbstractSyntaxNode class, but more subtly shown in NullNode and ExpressionNode. More detail is described within these classes; however, a quick description is as follows: ExpressionNodes are only allowed to have ExpressionNodes as chilren. NullNodes are an implementation of the Null Object paradigm shown here.
Since:
0.3.0
